cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Library Interoperability Performance Evaluation Dataset
abstract: This dataset documents a systematic evaluation of seven open‑source QUIC
  implementations by measuring file transfer throughput and energy consumption under
  varying bandwidth limits and test file sizes. The methodology involved automated
  server and client runs that synchronized start/stop events, logged timestamps, SHA‑1
  checksums, and power usage for each repetition. Evaluation scripts aggregated per‑run
  metrics to compute mean goodput, success rates, and timing statistics, producing
  JSON summaries and visualizations of the results.
